k
\mathbb{P}\left(\sum X_i=k\right)={1\over M^N}\sum_j (-1)^j{N\choose j}{k-jM-1\choose k-jM-N}.
k=27
N=10
M=6
{1\over 6^{10}}\left[{10\choose 0}{26\choose 17}-{10\choose 1}{20\choose 11}+{10\choose 2}{14\choose 5}\right] ={2665\over 104976}\approx 0.0254.
E(X_i)= \frac{M+1}{2}
E(X_i^2)=\frac{1}{M}\sum_{k=1}^M k^2 = \frac{(M+1)(2M+1)}{6} \Rightarrow Var(X_i)=\frac{M^2-1}{12}
Z = \sum_{i=1}^N X_i
\mu = N \frac{M+1}{2}
\sigma^2 = N \frac{M^2-1}{12} 
